<br><i>Never miss a good chance to shut up.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 5:52:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=229.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Shrug.</span><hr size=1> Dear Robin Goodfellow:<br>
<br>
First off, don't make a mountain out of a molehill...if you can read carefully and accurately - which I'm sure you can given the articulation exhibited in your post - you will see that I did not call Shintou's rants racist.<br>
<br>
I said:<br>
<br>
&quot;What you are exhibiting is intolerance...which is a degree or two away from racism. The difference between the two is who the hatred is aimed at (a race of peoples based on genetic makeup or a cultural/social group based on ideology). It's ugly, and it has no place in this world let alone a frickin game.&quot;<br>
<br>
There is a distinct difference between intolerance and racism, however the two are related in that they are both expressions of disdain, predjudice and criticism at different types of groups.  Anyone with any literary sense would see that Shintou's initial comments are intolerant to people outside of his chosen group.  Comments such as &quot;pack up and leave our server&quot;, &quot;there is not place for you here&quot; etc...etc...ad nauseaum are beyond someone expressing their opinion...they are examples of intolerance.  And I beg you or anyone to differ.<br>
<br>
Stating that I said Shintou's comments are racist is quite inaccurate and offensive.  His comments were however, blatantly intolerant of his deemed subset of the server's population that he dubbed non-roleplayers or powergamers.<br>
<br>
You stated:<br>
&quot;Further, to quote Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr., being a fanatic or an extremist is not always bad: &quot;...the question is not whether we will be extremists, but what kind of extremists we will be&quot; (&quot;Letter from Birmingham Jail&quot;).<br>
<br>
If Shin is a fanatic for roleplaying, what kind of extremist does that make you?&quot;<br>
<br>
While a little overwrought, the MLK quote doesn't necessarily work the way you would like it to.  <br>
<br>
True, being an extremist is not always a bad thing...but when it leads a person or group of persons to persecute another person or group of persons, it is a bad thing.  Read through every one of of Shin's initial diatribes and you will see something to the effect of &quot;if you do not fit such and such acceptable group A or are like unacceptable group B you have no place here.&quot;  Is that stating an opinion?  Is that what you would call opening up an inviting discussion?  Does that type of branding leave the targetted group much room for rebuttal other than putting them in a defensive posture?<br>
<br>
Read my post(s) and you'll see that what I am asking for - or perhaps &quot;fanatical&quot; for - is fricking tolerance.  This is a game.  A GAME.  People come here to play...to PLAY the way they want.  If they break the rules of the game, as defined by Sony/Verant, they are dealt with.  Otherwise, they can play how they choose to play, whether this is a roleplay PREFERRED server or not.<br>
<br>
For the record, I don't think Shin is a nazi, a fanatic, a jerk-off or anything of that order.  In my multiple posts I never once referred to him, or anyone else for that matter, in such terms.  If he wants to get into his roleplaying at a very deep level, more power to him.  I do however, reject the tone of intolerance that was blasted at various members of the FV community.<br>
<br>
And also for the record, Mr./Mrs./Ms. Robin Goodfellow, I am not an American, and perhaps you should refrain from using convenient paradigmns to taint another's comments and reasoning - which is what you tried to do.<br>
<br>
I have my own quote:  &quot;Live and let live.&quot;<br>
<br>
Check it out sometime,<br>
<br>
Rexfelix<br>
<br>
